CDFglobalAttributes.Descriptor: RPW-LFR-SURV-BP2> RPW Low Frequency Receiver Basic parameters set 2 data in Survey mode
CDFglobalAttributes.TEXT: This file contains RPW LFR level 2R Survey BP2 data of the current test.
CDFglobalAttributes.Logical_source_description: Solar Orbiter Radio and Plasma Wave, Level 2 Low Frequency Receiver (LFR) Basic Parameter Set 2 (BP2) Data in Survey Mode
CDFglobalAttributes.Rules_of_use: Data provided are publicly available. If used in presentations or publications, please acknowledge Solar Orbiter/RPW Investigation (M. Maksimovic, PIs). Please read carefully the caveats attached to the data. For reporting purposes, we request bibliography information for any publication, etc., using these data. Please send information on the use of this data to: M. Maksimovic (PI).
CDFglobalAttributes.Acknowledgement: The authors are pleased to acknowledge the Solar Orbiter/RPW Investigation (M. Maksimovic, PIs) for access to data.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Quality flag
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flag to indicate the quality of the data

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Bitmask flag
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flag to indicate any context information or status at the receiver or experiment level

VarAttributes.CATDESC: LFR common parameters and BIAS status info relevancy flag
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flag to indicate the relevancy of LFR common parameters (SP0/1, R0/1/2, BW) and BIAS STATUS INFO which can be non representative for the first packet following a change in those parameters.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: LFR survey mode (0 for normal mode, 1 for burst mode)
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flag to indicate if the receiver in the SURVEY_BURST (=1) or SURVEY_NORMAL (=0) mode

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Sampling frequency of the BP2
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Index to indicate the sampling frequency of the BP2 : F0, F1 or F2 in order to use only one skeleton for the 3 normal mode bp2 products of ICD.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of multiplexer setting.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the mode of BIAS multiplexer for a set of BP2 parameters. Possible values are 0 : Standard operation. 1 : Probe 1 fails. 2 : Probe 2 fails. 3 : Probe 3 fails. 4 : Calibration mode 0. 5 : Calibration mode 1. 6 : Calibration mode 2. 7 : Calibration mode 3.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of enable/disable HV (+- 100V).
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the status of BIAS HV. Possible values are DISABLED = 0. ENABLED = 1.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of enable/disable BIAS 1.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the status of BIAS probe 1. Possible values are DISABLED = 0. ENABLED = 1.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of enable/disable BIAS 2.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the status of BIAS probe 2. Possible values are DISABLED = 0. ENABLED = 1.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of enable/disable BIAS 3.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the status of BIAS probe 3. Possible values are DISABLED = 0. ENABLED = 1.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of BIAS status.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the status of BIAS. Possible values are OFF = 0 - Power line off. ON = 1 - Power line on.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: BIAS Works/BIAS Fails configuration.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Number of BP2 sets read for a given sampling frequency(F0, F1 or F2).
VarAttributes.FIELDNAM: CCSDS CUC format LFR time, coarse and fine parts
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: This indicates how many sets of BP1 have been read. Expected numbers for NORMAL MODE are 11 for F0, 13 for F1 and 12 for F2. Expected numbers for BURST MODE are 22 for F0 and 26 for F1.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Elapsed Time of the onboard clock
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Spaceraft Elapsed Time

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Time synchronisation flag
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flag to indicate if the local time is synchronized with the RPW DPU clock or not. Possible values: synchronized=0, not synchronized=1. This flag is extracted from ACQUISITION_TIME in L0 packets, it is the MSB of the CUC time.
